  "textPreview": "Free June 9 event: How to win brand visibility when AI decides what gets seen →\nSolutions\nTools\nResources\nPricing\nEN\nSign in\nRequest a demo\nStart free trial\nMove to SE Ranking without losing what you’ve built\n\nYour projects, keywords, and historical rankings come with you. What changes is the quality of your data and coverage: traditional search, AI visibility, traffic, and social metrics for a better understanding of your digital ecosystem\n\nStart migration\nTalk to our team\n\nNo credit card required\n\nImport projects and keyword data\nPreserve historical ranking insights\nGet support for complex migrations\nMigration paths from the tools you’re likely coming from\n\nWhat you can bring over depends on where you’re coming from. Most migrations combine direct imports, structured file transfers, or hands-on help from our team.\n\nFrom Semrush\n\nImport your keywords, projects, and ranking history with less manual setup\n\nFrom Ahrefs\n\nBring over your keyword lists and ranking data so your team picks up where it left off\n\nFrom AgencyAnalytics\n\nTransfer your tracker queries and historical data to keep your reporting intact\n\nFrom AccuRanker\n\nMove your keywords and tracking history to resume monitoring\n\nFrom Serpstat\n\nExport your core SEO data and retain the historical context your team relies on\n\nCSV or custom exports\n\nData in spreadsheets or a custom format? We’ll help you handle the file imports\n\nDon’t see your tool listed? Share what you’re working with, and we’ll review your export options and identify the most practical migration path.\nWhat moves over, and where we help fill the gaps\n\nSome things transfer directly, others need a bit of work. Either way, the core SEO data your team depends on comes with you\n\nWhat transfers automatically\n\nProjects and domains\n\nKeyword lists\n\nTags and keyword groups\n\nRanking history\n\nSearch engine and location settings\n\nCompetitor tracking foundations\n\nCore reporting inputs and monitoring setup\n\nWhat might require manual setup\n\nCustom report layouts\n",
